			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think I see what's happening. You should make your attribute shift registers 16 bits wide, to match the pattern registers, and update them in a similar fashion, by ORing a 00 or FF into the lower byte.<br /><br />Your current code is stomping your entire attribute shift register the moment the new tile gets merged in, but that tile won't hit the screen for 1-8 more pixels depending on the fine X scroll, hence your attributes appearing to be 7 pixels off.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
